# Git Rules

References:

- docs/coding-standards.md
- docs/development-roadmap.md

---

# Git Philosophy

Commits should be:

- Small
- Focused
- Reversible
- Understandable

One commit should represent one logical change.

---

# Branch Strategy

Main Branch

```text
main
```

Production-ready code only.

---

Development Branch

Optional:

```text
develop
```

Used for integration if needed.

---

Feature Branches

Pattern:

```text
feature/<feature-name>
```

Examples:

```text
feature/google-auth
feature/affiliate-links
feature/withdrawals
```

---

Bug Fix Branches

Pattern:

```text
bugfix/<issue-name>
```

Examples:

```text
bugfix/webhook-duplicate-processing
bugfix/order-status-update
```

---

Hotfix Branches

Pattern:

```text
hotfix/<issue-name>
```

Examples:

```text
hotfix/login-production-error
```

---

# Commit Message Convention

Use Conventional Commits.

---

Feature

```text
feat:
```

Example

```text
feat: add affiliate link generation
```

---

Fix

```text
fix:
```

Example

```text
fix: prevent duplicate webhook processing
```

---

Refactor

```text
refactor:
```

Example

```text
refactor: simplify withdrawal validation
```

---

Documentation

```text
docs:
```

Example

```text
docs: update api specification
```

---

Testing

```text
test:
```

Example

```text
test: add webhook integration tests
```

---

Chore

```text
chore:
```

Example

```text
chore: update dependencies
```

---

# Commit Size Rules

Preferred:

50 - 300 lines changed

Avoid:

Huge commits containing multiple unrelated features.

---

# Pull Request Rules

Each PR should:

- Solve one problem
- Have clear description
- Reference related documentation

---

PR Checklist

✓ Builds successfully

✓ Tests pass

✓ Documentation updated

✓ No secrets committed

---

# Documentation Before Merge

If feature changes:

- API
- Database
- User Flow
- Architecture

Verify documentation is updated before merge.

---

# Secret Management Rules

Never commit:

```text
.env
.env.local
.env.production
```

Never commit:

- JWT Secrets
- API Tokens
- OAuth Secrets
- Database Passwords

---

# Ignore Rules

Verify .gitignore includes:

```text
bin/
obj/
node_modules/
dist/
.vscode/
.env*
```

---

# Migration Rules

Database migrations must be committed.

Required:

✓ Migration File

✓ Snapshot File

Never commit partial migrations.

---

# Rebase Rules

Keep commit history clean.

Prefer:

```bash
git rebase
```

before merging long-lived branches.

---

# Release Tagging

Format:

```text
v1.0.0
v1.1.0
v1.2.0
```

Semantic Versioning

Major

```text
1.x.x
```

Breaking changes

Minor

```text
x.1.x
```

New features

Patch

```text
x.x.1
```

Bug fixes

---

